The paper deals with the stable marriage problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it deals with matching preferences of two groups. The paper proposes an approximation algorithm, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The problem is known to be NP-hard, which makes it relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis of the algorithm, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
